## Linux PCI Subsystem
The Linux PCI Subsystem provides a framework for detecting, configuring, and managing PCIe devices. 
It abstracts low-level PCIe operations and offers APIs that simplify driver development.
PCI drivers interact with the subsystem rather than accessing hardware directly.

